Tracking of the cancer of the prostate: to pass the test or not?
Indeed, the test of STEP would have sometimes erroneous results, with false negative results or of false-positives, which involve useless medical interventions.
What to make hesitate even more the already reticent men to pass from the screening tests.
To pass the test or not?
We asked for the opinion of two specialists.
In the studies conducted to the United States, there was much contamination between the reference groups, it is thus difficult to interpret these data and to have firm recommendations.
Another study, that one European, concluded with a difference in mortality between the patients who had a tracking and those which did not have of it.
This study also showed, with a follow-up after 12 years, which one has between 30 and 40% of more than chances to have metastases if one is not detected.
I thus recommend the test as from 50 years, or 40 years if one has a direct relative who already had a cancer of the prostate.
The men of origin Afro-American are also more at the risk.
The key is to once make the good decision one detected a cancer.
There are aggressive cancers and others which are indolent.
It is really necessary to render comprehensible with the patient the degree of risk of its cancer, by offering the possible options to him, by not treating necessarily cancers of the prostate which do not carry not reached to the long-term life, and while choosing rather, in these cases, for an active monitoring of the disease.
Today, much of men at whom one detects a cancer will not be treated, because their cancer is not aggressive and does not threaten their life.
One will suggest to them making active monitoring and if the disease progresses, one will offer a treatment to them.
More and more, one determines with precision of the criteria to decide which would have or should not be treated.
I thus recommend nevertheless to pass the test.
But the important thing is to have a discussion with its doctor to determine if one should pass it or not.
In collaboration with the international Company of urology, Movember created a tool which makes it possible to evaluate the pros and cons of the test of STEP.
One can download this document (in English for the moment, a translation will be offered soon) at this address: http://ca.movember.com/fr/mens-health/prostate-cancer-screening
To prevent the disease
There does not exist unfortunately miraculous formula to prevent cancer.
In spite of progress of research, the adoption of good practices of life remains the best means of reducing the risks to suffer from it.
It is estimated that if everyone ate well and moved sufficiently, one could prevent 30% of cancers.
“So nobody any more smoked, this rate would climb to at least 50%”, underlines André Beaulieu, spokesperson of the Canadian Company of cancer.
On the other hand, one evaluates that approximately 10% of cancers are caused by heredity.
Several remain also completely unexplained.
For the Canadian Company of cancer, the fight against the tobacco addiction remains a priority, in spite of the reduction amongst smokers.
The cigarette is related to 85% of the cases of lung cancer.
It constitutes also a risk factor for several others.
That harms the health of people enormously.
“Still today, there are 1.5 million smokers in Quebec”, the spokesperson André Beaulieu regrets.
Encouraging data: 10 years after the abandonment of the cigarette, the risk to die of a cancer falls of half.
The weight
The plumpness and obesity support also the appearance of the disease, according to the SCC.
They would increase the risks of cancer of the centre, the colon and the rectum, the oesophagus, the pancreas and the uterus.
“Research shows that the regular practice of the physical-activity during a whole life protects from cancer from the colon”, one adds.
Food
The organization also recommends to limit its consumption of red meat.
In too great quantity, it makes climb the risks to be reached of a cancer colorectal.
Pork-butcheries also, and they should be avoided.
The conservation of the meat by manuring, drying or salting can involve the formation of carcinogenic substances.
“These last can damage the cells of the organization and lead to the development of cancer”, one explains.
Vitamins
During last years, several scientists studied the bonds between the vitamin supplements and cancer.
Their research is not however conclusive for the moment.
Studies on the vitamin E are contradictory, according to the SCC.
Whereas one of them noted a reduction in the risks of cancer of the prostate, another an increase noted rather.
The effect of the vitamin D on cancer is not clearly established either.
In addition, Mr. Beaulieu insists on the importance of speaking about his concerns and his family antecedents with his doctor.
“To pass a screening test, that does not give cancer.”

