A Constitution with the forceps in Egypt
It is a new gamble of president Mohammed Morsi.
Whereas Egypt remains more divided than ever around the constitutional declaration, which grants temporarily the absolute powers to him, it decided to play its go-all.
Taking everyone of short, he announced, Wednesday, that the constituent Assembly would vote for her final text the following day.
