On the side of his partisans, one ensures that it is a means of finishing some as fast as possible with the institutional and political crisis, by accelerating the transition process.
A referendum should be organized in the fifteen days.
A very short period of time which obliges the Brothers to give up their project to explain the text, article by article, with the Egyptians.
For the President, it is also a way of finding a popular and democratic legitimacy whereas the dispute made fumes in all the country.
Mohammed Morsi seems convinced that the Egyptians will vote favorably, as it affirmed in an interview with the American weekly magazine Time.
The more so as this recourse to a precipitated vote is due of the ultimatum to the Egyptian people: “Either you vote for my text, or I keep the absolute powers”, those having supposedly to end after the adoption of the Constitution.
It is in a strange environment that 85 members of this constituent Assembly, with great islamist majority, voted for the text yesterday.
