The text, which was still in the train D " being voted yesterday evening, comprises 234 articles.
Objects of all the attentions, article 2 remains finally identical to that of the Constitution of 1971, stipulating that “the principles of the charia are the primary source of the right.”
The Salafist parties, for which L " establishment of Islamic law is a major claim, hoped to be able to replace “the principles” by “the rules”, which would have allowed a more strict application.
