These last days, a wave of protest is assembled against the low wages practised by the Walmart supermarkets and the famous chains of fast-food industry such as McDonald's, Burger King, Taco Bell, Wendy' S and Kentucky Fried Chicken.
For the moment, nobody can predict if this wave will gain in importance or to blow itself quickly.
These actions are supported by the trade unions and a certain number of associations of left.
Parallel to the modest wage increase that the basic employees at Walmart and in the chains of fast-food industry perceive, the organizers of the demonstrations wish to obtain the creation of trade unions.
This sector is not for the moment not covered by the trade union movement.
46 hundreds a year?
The demonstrations began last week, after Thanksgiving, “black Friday”, at the moment when a breaking rain of balances seizing million inhabitants fell down on America and starting scandals sometimes.
This day, some paid of the Walmart company, which employs in the world 2.2 million people, left their station to organize strike pickets with the trade unions and the activists of left in the stores of the company whose products are intended to the consumers of the modest and average classes.
Walmart markets all: layers with the shotguns via the batteries of car, the vacuum cleaners, eggs and milk.
The products are there on average 8% to 27% less expensive than in the large supermarkets.
This is why much of paid evil paid at Walmart make their races only on their workplace.
The price and the choice of the products did of Walmart one of the most powerful groups in the United States.
According to criticisms, Walmart can allow itself to sell its cheap products in particular because of the low wages of its employees.
The latter also complain about the difficult work conditions, for example lack of forklift trucks or scanners portable.
The participants of the manifestations of “black Friday” asked for a pay rise, they complained owing to the fact that the price of the medical insurance provided by the company had increased by 30 to 100 dollars per month.
For the basic employee at Walmart which touches 9.5 $ of the hour, it is a sum which it cannot allow.
Scientists of the Californian university of Berkley show that if Walmart increased the average wages with 12 $ of the hour, that would cost the group 3.2 billion dollars.
It is 1.1% of more than the EC what he currently spends.
If Walmart transferred all the wage increase on the shoulders from the consumers, each race in the store would total to them 46 hundreds more.
They will spend in one year only 12.39 dollars moreover than now.
The partisans of Walmart notice with satisfaction that the protests took place in only nine States and did not carry any damage to the group.
“Black Friday” continued in the stores of 8:00 the evening to midnight the following day and Walmart sold over this period 5000 articles at the second.
Its cases carried out in all 100 million transactions for “black Friday”.
The spokesperson of the company Dan Fogleman ensured in an interview the site of left Huffington Post that in very “less than five” employees of Walmart their stations had left and that the protest was only one “communications operation among so much of others” on behalf of the organizing trade union.
“Following Customer!”
The protests continued this week in New York and related to either the Walmart stores (in this progressive city, they are not very appreciated, this is why they are not established yet there) but McDonald's and other restaurants cheap.
McDonald's announces to sell billion portions and after they do not even give you a vacation disease and do not pay you the work which you made honestly!
Jumaane Williams, member of the Town council of New York
Currently, the minimum wage envisaged by the federal legislation and that of New York east of 7.25 $ of the hour.
Fast-food increase them with time, but little, on average its basic employees touches in New York 8.90 $ of the hour.
Nobody touches less than them in this city.
For me it is inconceivable to live with this sum in New York.
It was a time when almost a quarter of the American teenagers worked at McDonald's after the high school while living in their parents.
Few people saw their primary source of incomes there or wished to remain there for a long time.
Today, I find myself with interviewing employees of McDonald's which complain about having to live with these wages and sometimes having to nourish their children with.
In addition, on the forum of the newspaper Wall Street Journal one finds comments saying that it is irresponsible to make children if you do not know with what you will nourish them.
The demonstrators who launched the movement Thursday at 6:30 close to McDonald's of the 40e street and on Madison Avenue required that the cash clerks and the cooks of fast-food be at least paid 15 $ of the hour, that is to say a multiplication of more than twice than the current minimum wage.
They also asked so that trade unions in the sector of fast-food industry be created.
The American law prohibited with the administration there to prevent and to punish the protesters of a trade union by victimizations or dismissals.
