Fiete Hopf, orchestra conductor the 29 year old loses almost its shoes of fabric when it directs the orchestra with his gestures of a wild flexibility.
We are Monday evening, the Imbongi choral society repeats a new song in the room of music of the Institute of Medical Psychology of Heidelberg.
Fifty singers and singers from 23 to 69 years came, of the geneticist in human medicine to the house-husband.
“Om' Obani” is not an easy piece, each chorus-singer has different words, the whole in a very exotic language: the Zulu, a spoken language by 11 million people in South Africa, in Botswana, in Lesotho, in Malawi, in Mozambique and in certain areas of Swaziland.
To be helped to help itself
The ONUSIDA, the program of the United Nations of fight against AIDS, estimate that 34 million people throughout the world is reached disease.
23.5 million of them lives in the South of Africa.
Swaziland counts 245.000 infected people.
Moreover, more than 40% of the population is HIV positive.
180 orphans of the AIDS of the village of Esitjeni found godfathers in Germany thanks to association “Voices for Africa”.
70 of them attend an establishment of secondary education.
For 15 or 20 euros per less, one can become godfather.
This sum guarantees to the child of the money for the school, a school uniform and a daily hot meal in the center sucker.
Imbongi means into Zulu “storyteller of stories” or even “singer of praises”.
Nobody can usually speak the Bantu language in this area, but all can sing it.
Since nearly 10 years, the choral society repeats songs in this foreign language which it brought in Germany for now returning it to her native area: south of Africa.
Because with 8.733 kilometers as the crow flies of Heidelberg, in the North-West of the Kingdom of Swaziland, Esitjeni is, the village which depends on the vocal power of the German choral society.
40% people reached
The village counts approximately 2.000 inhabitants, some live in modest huts of straw or of ground and the majority of them is children.
More than 300 between them are orphan, because the VIH carried their parents.
In Esitjeni, one can observe with more small scale the evils who overpower Swaziland: the rate of infection with the highest VIH and the lowest life expectancy in the world according to the UNICEF.
The population practically never accepts the male circumcision, a measurement which however guarantees a proven reduction of the risk of infection of half.
More than 40% of the population of Swaziland is carrying the virus of the immunodeficiency and it is not rare to die in the middle of about thirty.
At the time of a travel of group in Africa in spring 2005, the choral society had been able to discover the village. Imbongis especially saw many children in the street with which it missed not only the parental care, but also quite simply all: food, clothing, education.
In a poor country, without school diploma, there is simply no prospect.
At the beginning, they were only some people who personally committed themselves pouring a few euros each year in order to be able to send a child to the school and to offer a hot meal per day to him.
But hardly one year later, the choral society founded “Voices for Africa”, an association which is since then occupied in an almost professional way of the orphans of the AIDS of Esitjeni.
Facts in connection with the infections sexually transmissible
Which are the sexually transmitted diseases most current?
Among STI bacterial, one counts syphilis, chlamydiées and the blennorrhoea (or gonorrhoea).
STI current are the VIH, the virus of the human papilloma, the genital herpes or hepatitis.
The pubic louses and the scale belong to STI parasitic.
Which are the groups mainly concerned?
Syphilis and the blennorrhoea often appear at the men who have sexual relationships with other men.
The Institute Robert-Koch estimates that the sexual contacts between men are at the origin of at least four cases of syphilises on five declared in Germany.
In the adult heterosexuals, the infections related to chlamydiées, the trichomonase, the candidiasis (fungic), the blennorrhoea and the virus of the human papilloma are current sexually transmitted diseases.
The rate of propagation of the VIH between adult heterosexuals is relatively low in Germany. However, some 20% of the new infections with the VIH are observed within this group.
In the young people, one observes a rate of infections related to chlamydiées appreciably higher than at the other groups of population.
According to European statements, the three quarters of all the infections relate to the young ages from 15 to 25 years.
Moreover, in Germany, the virus of the human papilloma is current in the young people.
Which is the evolution amongst infections?
It is not obligatory to declare all the sexually transmitted diseases.
According to the Institute Robert-Koch, the number of the cases of syphilis more than doubled in 10 years: the figure passed from 1.967 in 2001 to 3.698 in 2011.
Since 2007, the number of the new infections with the VIH falls.
In 2011, there were approximately 2.700 cases.
That represents a reduction in a tenth compared to the previous year.
Which are the symptoms of a sexual disease?
The infectious diseases can cause abscesses on the level as of genitals, of the urinary pains, the vaginal discharge, the pains to the stomach as well as the appearance of buttons and warts.
However, they regularly do not involve any pain or another symptom and thus remain hidden.
How to protect itself?
The condoms can decrease the risk of infection, but they do not protect at 100%.
The reason is that the disease-causing agents of the sexually transmitted diseases can be also transmitted by lubricating infection or close body contacts.
The experts thus recommend to any person often changing sexual partners to pass regularly from the examinations.
Most STI quickly detected can be cured and the late after-effects can be avoided.
Thanks to sponsorships, with the gifts, but especially at the funds which the chorus-singers thanks to their voices collect through whole Germany, the means accumulate.
