That does not go from oneself, because even if the disease is quite visible in all the country, it remains a subject taboo.
A king and his 14 wives
“The AIDS is a true taboo”, explains Annette Lennartz, “because it is a subject which touches sexuality.”
They is rather curious, coming from a country whose king has 14 official wives.
The last absolute monarch of the Black Africa, the King Mswati III, is known for his excessive lifestyle.
Polygamy instead of the democracy.
These manners sanctioned by the State, inter alia, are responsible for the fast propagation of the VIH observed these last decades.
Migrant worker also disseminated the virus through the country.
One however finds condoms with each corner of street, adds Annette Lennartz, “but almost nobody uses them.
