The travel in the Talysh mountains is of a dishevelled romanticism.
With the turning of the many turnings of the road, the small bus jolts along timbered hills, of torrential rivers and modest farms.
All is green and fertile, one would believe oneself almost in the Black Forest.
But we are here in the major South of Azerbaijan, the border with Iran is only with a few kilometers.
It is here that the Caucasian ethnic group of the name of Talysh lives, by the way which large-thing is not known, if it is not that they speak perfectly the Persan one and the Azeri and that they have a very great longevity.
Terminus: Lerik.
The plastronne small town with its too aggressive architecture of the Soviet era which does not agree at all with the picturesque landscape of mountain.
The European tourists are rare here, the way since the capital of Azerbaijan, Bakou, is well too painful.
It takes eight hours to traverse the 323 kilometers, because the road has only one way.
The province did not benefit yet from the legendary wealth that the country must with its crude oil reserves in the Caspian Sea.
However, Pilata Fatulayeva, 48 years, is persuaded that Lerik has the potential to become a tourist place.
“Bakou became celebrates in May thanks to the competition of Eurovision, and the next year, there will be here the festival of the oldest people of the world”, explains Fatulayeva.
It is director of the museum of longevity, the only museum of the kind in the world.
One can discover there the life of approximately eight tens of Talysh of the area which have more than 100 years. Fatulayeva shows us a monochrome photo.
Here my grandfather, it reached the 120 years age.
To have still a child at 136 years
But the star discussed of the museum is Șirali Müslümov, a shepherd who would have been 168 years old.
There does not exist however birth certificate.
And when it is thought that the oldest documented person was 122 years old, the age of Müslümov seems more than doubtful.
“It was born in 1805 in this area, it died in 1973”, Fatulayeva specifies.
The man would have married three times and it would have had 23 children. At the 136 years age, it would have still designed a girl.
Would Șirali Müslümov have been mistaken in a few decades by calculating its age?
Rembrandt Scholz, gerontologist at the Institute Max-Planck de Rostock, also heard to him of the man at the great age of Central Asia.
“Surprisingly old people also live in certain areas of China, in Japan or in the valley of Hunza in Pakistan”, explains Scholz, “in Sardinia also, there are men who live incredibly old.”
However, it is impossible to establish a scientific proof because of the inexistence of the documents, not counting there was no civil register.
Each day, glass of melted butter
It is nevertheless in fact that people of the area of Lerik often reach an age worthy of the patriarchs of the Bible.
Currently, 20 people have more than 100 years.
Which is thus the reason of longevity in the South of this country?
Farid Mugimzadeh, the Azeri tourist guide, explains that Talysh have particular genes.
