It is, without any doubt, one of the most former patients of the unit of the VIH of the civil hospital of Guadalajara (HCG), in which it was found in 1994 after many battles.
Fabrizio has lived with the virus of the human immunodeficiency (VIH) for 22 years, something of difficult to imagine at the beginning of the Nineties, where there were many doubts, little choice of treatment and more marks.
Then, even the director of a private clinic of the IMSS avoided telling him goodbye “because it was without voice”.
In this time, to have the AIDS was synonymous with death.
Today, it is possible to survive this syndrome and to have a good quality of life.
However, being unaware of their disease, of many people still arrive when the virus already caused damage, “exhausted” their immune system and are opportunist victims of infections.
31 years after the appearance of the AIDS in the world, in all the cases after the first announced cases, “the great victory is today that the survival of a patient having begun a treatment the convenient period and survival from the population in general are exactly the same one”, the chief of the unit of the VIH of the HCG indicated, Jaime Andrade Villanueva and it takes for reference which this information was validated in April of this year in a prestigious scientific publication.
The infectiologist and expert in VIH/sida, Andrade Villanueva, commented on that since 2008, the scientists concluded that the AIDS was not any more one fatal disease, but that the number of years of survival and quality of life depended on the level on assignment on the immune system which the patients presented at the time of the diagnosis, with better prospects for those not consuming drugs: up to 30 years for a rate of CD4 of 200 and up to 50 years for those reaching a rate of 500 CD4.
To speak simply, that means that for somebody who would receive a positive diagnosis VIH at 25 years, “as long as it will remain under control, will be able to live without problems up to 75 years”, explained the questioned scientist.
In order to replace this progress in its context, it is necessary to know that the life expectancy of the Mexicans is 76 years today on average.
If it is true that mortality decreased these last years significantly, in the case of Mexico, the number of people deceased of the continuations of the AIDS passed from 6.678 cases in 2007 to 4.862 in 2011 (according to the annual report of ONUSIDA), but it is also true that, since the appearance of the AIDS, 60% of the patients listed on the national database died.
Only in Jalisco, 255 people died in 2011, and there were 187 deaths until May this year; however, it is ensured us that the access to the antirétroviraux drugs is universal since 2005.
Then why y-a it still of the deaths?
I think that the problem does not come from the access to the treatment.
It is as that I see it, it is what occurred in our hospital.
Over the 12 last years at least, we never missed drugs, the problem is that the patients arrive at very advanced stages because they do not know that they are infected, or then they learn it at stages advanced from the disease.
It gives us to an indisputable fact “new patients on ten arrive whereas they present already an opportunist infection, which it is necessary to have a greater impact on total mortality, it is to carry out earlier diagnoses and, for that, it is necessary to propose screening tests in a massive way, with all the people who ask it”.
The specialists and the members of the Council of State of prevention of the AIDS of Jalisco (Coesida) agree on its proposal, just as the patients themselves, like Fabrizio, who has to make his screening test in a private laboratory, simply because a friend had done it and that, in spite of his young age, it was already carrying the AIDS and suffered from the sarcoma from Kaposi, a cancerous tumour which is one of the current complications.
Any exchange when you learn that you have the AIDS.
Some think that they will die and wants nothing to know.
“If I will die, it is better that I burst myself three times per week”, it they say is not my case.
The change was beneficial, I eat well, I do exercise, I take my medicines.
To date, his/her parents know only that he suffers from a cancer.
I have a normal life, like no matter whom of other.
“I work, I have many activities, I travel, I have an active sex life, but jointly responsible, I pay attention to me and the other person”, Fabrizio tells, who agreed to share his intimacy with MILENIO JALISCO to help, thanks to its testimony, those which are afraid today, at the time of the walk of the World Day against the AIDS.
That they make the test, if they took chances, more they will know early if they are HIV positive and better it is, and if they have already the diagnosis, it is necessary that they know that one can live like everyone, while being responsible.
Its message summarizes the slogan of the battle against the AIDS in this year 2012.
Condoms on the counter
It there has many gaps between the programs of health and the ordinary citizen, supports Ricardo Salazar, journalist of Guadalajara which embraced the cause of the VIH.
And largest resides in the prevention.
In all the places dedicated to that, “one actually increased the distribution of the condoms, before one gave of them us one or two, now one gives us packages of one hundred of them, it is very well, but it results from it, that still today, some do not have access to the condoms”, he affirms.
Among most vulnerable to the new infections, one finds the teenagers.
The question: “What will you make some? ”, posed with sarcastic remark and value judgments by the social workers, the careers advisers, the pharmacists and the health professionals, is the question which the teenagers do not have desire for hearing, the journalist ensures.
He proposes to reorientate this ineffective distribution; that the condoms are not only sold with the counters, but that one finds them in the distributors of the public toilets and the places which attend the young people.
It is not a question of encouraging promiscuity.
It is not a question either of paying them the girls and the motel, as had answered the governor Emilio González when it had been asked to him whether there would be a distribution of the condoms within his administration.
“It is not as that which sexuality functions, best is to sexually provide condoms to the already active people”, he underlined.
Figures with Jalisco
13.435 cumulated cases are counted (12.158 from the AIDS and 1.317 of the VIH).
The State is the 4th State of the country of number of the new cases and cumulated cases of AIDS and 13th for the number of the patients of the VIH.
92% of the contaminations are done by sexual way, 6% per blood way and 2% per perinatal way.
